# Supabase and data layer

Read **agents.md** section "How data should work" and **CLAUDE.md** "Data and auth rules".

## Responsibilities

- **Browser:** supabaseService resolves restaurant context from session (owner) or slug/id (customer). All UI reads/writes go here.
- **Server API routes:** supabase-admin only; service role env var never in Vite client bundle.
- **Schema:** supabase/schema.sql defines tables, RLS, RPCs — update schema, types, and service mappings together.

## Menu persistence

saveMenu is a full sync: upsert all categories/dishes, delete anything not in the payload. Use explicit id lists for deletes — avoid fragile filter strings.

## Schema changes workflow

Update schema file → push via db:push or SQL editor → adjust database.types and types.ts → extend service layer → update UI field mapping.

Do not extend mockData.ts for new features.
